parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spark Plug Ejection from Cylinder Head
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ejection of spark plugs from the cylinder head can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to engine fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Spark plug blows out of the engine
a fire hazard due to unburned fuel igniting from the coil ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine while driving or idling can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle loses power steering or brakes.
symptoms: Engine stalling while driving or idling

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks from the head gasket can cause engine fires, especially if the oil drips onto the hot exhaust system, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the head gasket
oil collecting in the brush shield on the exhaust Y-connection

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Injector Failure and Fuel Tank Liner Delamination
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel injector failure and fuel tank liner delamination can cause sudden loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Fuel injector sensor failure can cause sudden acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
Fuel gauge malfunction can cause driver confusion, leading to accidents or running out of fuel.
Spark plug failure can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In extreme cases, it can also cause fires.
Diesel engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: black clouds of smoke from the exhaust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Accelerator failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or acceleration, leading to accidents or near-misses.
